Description of incident: A July 25 office burglary resulted in the theft of at least 33 laptops and iPads. The personal information of an unspecified number of former employees may have been affected.UPDATE (11/28/2012): The laptops contained employee names, Social Security numbers, addresses, dates of birth, passport numbers, credit card information, bank account numbers, and possibly life insurance dependent information.  The IT department remotely locked access to the devices after discovering they had been stolen earlier in the same day.
